  "prompt": "When will Mu sigma pay the joining bonus of 5L? I am joining in Aug 2016!",
  "response": "Congratulations on your upcoming role at Mu Sigma!\n\nRegarding the **joining bonus of \u20b95 lakhs**, the payment schedule can vary based on company policies and individual agreements. Typically, joining bonuses are paid out according to the terms outlined in your offer letter or employment contract. Common practices include:\n\n1. **Upon Joining**: Some companies disburse the bonus shortly after you start your employment.\n2. **After Probation Period**: The bonus might be paid after successfully completing a probationary period, which can range from 3 to 6 months.\n3. **In Installments**: Occasionally, bonuses are split and paid in multiple installments over your initial months with the company.\n\n**Steps You Can Take:**\n\n1. **Review Your Offer Letter**: Check the document you received when you accepted the offer. It should detail the bonus payment terms.\n2. **Contact HR**: Reach out directly to the Human Resources department at Mu Sigma. They can provide specific information regarding your bonus payout schedule.\n3. **Speak with Your Recruiter**: If you were in touch with a recruitment representative during your hiring process, they might also have insights or can direct you to the appropriate contact.\n\nIf you joined in **August 2016**, and if you're referring to a past bonus, it's possible there might have been an oversight or delay. In such cases:\n\n1. **Document Your Communication**: Keep records of all communications regarding your bonus.\n2. **Follow Up Professionally**: Send a polite inquiry to your HR representative or manager addressing your concern.\n3. **Seek Assistance if Needed**: If you don't receive a satisfactory response, consider reaching out to higher management or the employee relations department.\n\nI hope this helps, and best wishes for your journey with Mu Sigma!",
